Steps to Complete the Tasks:
Task-1: Develop the Website
Review the Designs

Check the screens from Assignment-1 and note the layout, colors, typography, and elements used.
Set Up the Project Folder

Create a folder for your project (e.g., assignment_2).
Inside, create the following files:
index.html (Main HTML file)
style.css (CSS file for styling)
Write HTML Structure

Use <header>, <nav>, <section>, <footer>, etc., to structure the webpage.
Add necessary elements like buttons, images, and links based on your design.
Apply CSS Styling

Style the page using style.css.
Use Flexbox or Grid for layouts.
Apply colors, fonts, and spacing as per the design.
Test Responsiveness

Use media queries (@media) to make the design responsive for mobile and desktop views.
Task-2: Upload Code in assignment_2 Folder
Ensure All Files Are in assignment_2

The folder should contain:
index.html
style.css
Any images (images/ folder)
Other assets if needed (JS, fonts)
Upload the Folder

If submitting online, use the given platform (Google Drive, GitHub, or your college portal).
If submitting via USB, copy assignment_2 and ensure everything is included.
Need Help?
Let me know if you need a sample HTML & CSS template or help with specific design issues!







