To develop a website using HTML & CSS based on the screens designed in Assignment-1, follow these structured steps:

1. Set Up the Project Folder
Create a new folder assignment_2.
Inside it, create:
index.html (Main HTML file)
style.css (CSS file for styling)
images/ (Folder for images, if needed)
assets/ (Optional for fonts, icons, or scripts)
2. Build the HTML Structure (index.html)
Write clean, semantic HTML. Example:

html
Copy
Edit
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Services</a></li>
                <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <section class="hero">
        <h2>Main Heading</h2>
        <p>Short description goes here.</p>
        <a href="#" class="btn">Learn More</a>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>Â© 2025 My Website. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
3. Apply CSS Styling (style.css)
Design the page to match your Assignment-1 layout.

css
Copy
Edit
/* Reset Styles */
* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

/* Header Styling */
header {
    background: #333;
    color: white;
    padding: 15px;
    text-align: center;
}

nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
}

nav ul li a {
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
}

/* Hero Section */
.hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 50px;
    background: #f4f4f4;
}

.hero .btn {
    background: blue;
    color: white;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    text-decoration: none;
}

/* Footer */
footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
    background: #222;
    color: white;
    margin-top: 30px;
}
4. Test Responsiveness
Use Flexbox or CSS Grid.
Add media queries to adjust for mobile devices.
Example:

css
Copy
Edit
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    nav ul {
        flex-direction: column;
        text-align: center;
    }
}
